TopicTitle: [1.4.x] BDArmory Continued v1.2.2.2 [8/8/2018] + Vessel Mover, Camera Tools, BDMk22, Destruction Effects, Burn Together

Articles.Content:
Just now, Murican_Jeb said:

When you started making stories

hahahahahahaha I wish!
Does this fix the issue with the nukes from NKD blowing the planes up when detonating?

Okay, gotta say I think I'm going to really love the new modular missiles and the physics extender. I decided to really give it a test (need to modify the range of the radar now), and I made a BVRAAM. The AI picked and fired it as soon as the enemy fighter was visible on radar. Once I extend the radar range I'll give it another good test.

Well, once I figure out how to extend the radar range.

1 hour ago, Ct9ars said:

Does this fix the issue with the nukes from NKD blowing the planes up when detonating?

You're gonna need to take that up with Harpwner.

But I highly doubt that this will change that in the slightest. You can always edit the CFG to make the blast radius smaller.

Edited March 27, 2017 by stickman939

When a vessel is using guard mode they cant fire any missiles further than 10km away, but as soon as their target is within 10km they shoot their missiles. However when I pilot the craft my self I can lock and fire a missile further than 10km, is this a bug?

Just now, Wolf123 said:

When a vessel is using guard mode they cant fire any missiles further than 10km away, but as soon as their target is within 10km they shoot their missiles. However when I pilot the craft my self I can lock and fire a missile further than 10km, is this a bug? 

The guard's probably just really cautious and doesn't want to waste it's stuff.

6 minutes ago, Wolf123 said:

When a vessel is using guard mode they cant fire any missiles further than 10km away, but as soon as their target is within 10km they shoot their missiles. However when I pilot the craft my self I can lock and fire a missile further than 10km, is this a bug? 

Nvm, I think its the max static launch range...

Hi all,

I just updated the pre-release for 1.2.9 @Guard13007 found a bug yesterday and I have fixed it (it was related with the new localization system implemented in 1.2.9).

You can download it from https://github.com/PapaJoesSoup/BDArmory/releases/tag/v.2.0.0-KSPv1.2.9

BTW I'm thinking to open a King of the Hill challenge (like ASC) for this pre-release version. What do you think?

 

8 minutes ago, Wolf123 said:

When a vessel is using guard mode they cant fire any missiles further than 10km away, but as soon as their target is within 10km they shoot their missiles. However when I pilot the craft my self I can lock and fire a missile further than 10km, is this a bug? 

I know there are dozens of hard coded values on the code. It might be an inconsistency.

One interesting bug I found while combat testing my Destroyer vs my Battleship; Apparently the M1 Abrams turret has the floatation properties of a pre-1.0 air intake. That thing went about 500 meters up in the air before I shot it down with a missile.

RE the above and @ the rest of the team , there's something very odd going on with the Abrams turret, a buoyancy value of minus 10 should have it sink like a stone but no it  still bobs like it's made of styrofoam,  Through some trickery i managed to attach some parts that allows me to artificially increase the mass as i choose,  the Abrams turret weighs 2 tonne as stock which is way too light anyway, but regardless,  it took an additional 11 tonne to successfully sink the damn thing and even then the barrel was still providing a massive amount of positive buoyancy.  This for reference was after destroying the drag cubes and any stored mm cache so it was all fresh info. There seems to be only one option left that being to extract it and find out whats going on, sadly debug stuff is no longer accurately reporting colliders so any info it gives is suspect.  No biggy though as you know I do this a dozen times a day, if i find anything that can be improved upon ( apart from the dull as dishwater appearance (my M1 from SM AFv's below) ) I'll push the results.

Spoiler

Edit sometime later and it is fixed, Sometime during the many versions of BDA and KSP that turret had been through without being touched  the base collider had become rotated 180 so it was pointing vertically and the game in it's infinite wisdom decided that it needed a sphere collider! So it had this great big buoyant sphere that only the game could see.  Definitely sinks now as it should.
